PN,39705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F397A1777036267
OL,3,CNew tribute unveiled to 'Canary Girls'
OL,4,Cwho kept Britain's war machine going
OL,6,FBuckshaw Village is built on the site
OL,7,Fof the Royal Ordnance Factory Chorley,
OL,8,Fwhich, in the Second World War, was
OL,9,FBritain's largest ammunition filling
OL,10,Ffactory.
OL,12,FAt its height, 30, 000 people, mainly
OL,13,Fwomen, worked there.
OL,15,FThe memorial board was unveiled not
OL,16,Fonly in honour of the Canary Girls,
OL,17,Fbut also to share their story with
OL,18,Ffuture generations.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
